    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix resource cleanup issue in compute_nr_prach_seq function\n\n### Summary\nThe function `compute_nr_prach_seq` was using `DevAssert` for bounds checking, which causes abrupt termination when assertions fail. This prevents proper cleanup of resources that might have been allocated upstream. This change replaces the `DevAssert` calls with proper error checking that allows for graceful error handling.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/NR_TRANSPORT/nr_prach_common.c`: Replaced `DevAssert` calls with bounds checking that returns early on error, added error logging, and ensured proper function exit.\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen calling `compute_nr_prach_seq()` with invalid parameters that cause the bounds checking to fail, the previous implementation would cause the program to exit abruptly via `DevAssert`. This prevented any upstream code from performing proper resource cleanup. With this fix, the function now returns gracefully, allowing calling code to handle the error condition and perform necessary cleanup.\n\nThe issue can be observed when:\n1. `compute_nr_prach_seq` is called with parameters that result in an out-of-bounds index\n2. The function encounters the bounds violation and previously would call `DevAssert`\n3. This would cause abrupt termination without allowing proper resource cleanup\n\nAfter this fix, the function will log the error and return early, allowing the calling code to handle the error condition appropriately.\n"
}